greenmirror.server

Class AbstractTransition<E extends Node,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.animation.Animation
      • javafx.animation.Transition
        • greenmirror.server.AbstractTransition<E,T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoublePropertyTransition, ImageFxWrapper.ImageTransition, TextFxWrapper.TextTransition

    public abstract class AbstractTransition<E extends Node,T>
extends Transition
    A Transition extension that holds features used by all subclasses. These are only simple ones: getters and setters for the 'from' value (the starting value), the 'to' value (the final value), the node to which the transition applies, the duration of the transition and the original opacity.

    The interpolate(double) method is the important one and has to be implemented by extending classes.

    Author:
    Karim El Assal
    See Also:
    Transition
